Hand Cricket is a fun and interactive implementation of the classic game using real-time hand tracking and computer vision. 
This project utilizes the MediaPipe library for hand landmark detection, allowing players to make their moves by showing their hand gestures to the camera.

Features:
~ Real-time hand landmark detection using MediaPipe.
~ Interactive gameplay with dynamic score tracking.
~ Computer opponent with randomized moves.
~ Option to choose between odd and even for determining the winner.

Requirements:
~ Python 3.x
~ OpenCV
~ MediaPipe
~ NumPy
~ Matplotlib

How To Play:
1. Start the Program.
2. Follow the on-screen instructions to choose between odd and even and play your turn.
3. Use hand gestures to make your move.
4. The computer will randomly generate its move.
5. Enjoy the game and try to beat the computer!

Credits:
This project uses the MediaPipe library for hand tracking and landmark detection.
